        <h2 id = "mac-cheese">Recipe #1: <em>Mac n Cheese</em></h2>
        
        
        <ul>
            <li>Time: 30 minutes</li>
            <li>Serves: 4</li>
        </ul>
        
        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Ingredients</th>
                    <th>Quantity</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td>Macaroni</td>
                <td> 1 cup</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Butter</td>
                <td> 1 tbsp</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Flour</td>
                <td> 1 cup</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Salt</td>
                <td> 2-3 tsp</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Black Pepper</td>
                <td> 1 tsp</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Milk</td>
                <td> 2/3 cups</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Shredded Cheese</td>
                <td> 1/2 cup</td>
            </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        
        <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Preheat oven to 375<br>
        <strong>Step 2:</strong> Cook Macaroni<br>
        <strong>Step 3:</strong> Make Roux<br>
        <strong>Step 4:</strong> Add Milk an Cheese<br>
        <strong>Step 5:</strong> Pour into baking dish
        </p>
        
    <p><em>Source: <a href="https://tastesbetterfromscratch.com/homemade-mac-and-cheese/">Mac and Cheese Recipe</a></em></p>
    
    <h2 id ="egg">Recipe #2: <em>Scrambled Eggs</em></h2>
        
        
        <ul>
            <li>Time: 10-15 minutes</li>
            <li>Serves: 2</li>
        </ul>
        
        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Ingredients</th>
                    <th>Quantity</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td>Eggs</td>
                <td> 4</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Salt</td>
                <td> 1 1/2 tsp</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Pepper</td>
                <td> 1 tsp</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Milk</td>
                <td> 3 tbsp tsp</td>
            </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        
        <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Preheat stove to medium heat<br>
        <strong>Step 2:</strong> Place pan on stovetop<br>
        <strong>Step 3:</strong> add 3 tbsp of olive oil<br>
        <strong>Step 4:</strong> add eggs, milk, salt and pepper into 
        a bowl<br>
        <strong>Step 5:</strong> Stir ingredients in bowl together<br>
        <strong>Step 6:</strong> When pan is heated, pour egg contents into pan and flip when egg is formed<br>
        <strong>Step 7:</strong> Break egg into smaller pieces and enjoy!
        </p>
        
    <p><em>Source: <a href="https://www.eggs.ca/recipes/simple-scrambled-eggs">Scrambled Eggs Recipe</a></em></p>
    
    <h2 id ="grilled">Recipe #3: <em>Grilled Cheese</em></h2>
        
        
        <ul>
            <li>Time: approx 20 minutes</li>
            <li>Serves: 1-2</li>
        </ul>
        
        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Ingredients</th>
                    <th>Quantity</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td>Bread</td>
                <td> 4 slices</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Cheese</td>
                <td> 2 slices</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Bacon</td>
                <td> 2 slices</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Lunch Meat</td>
                <td> 3 slices</td>
            </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        
        <p><em>Defrost all ingredients before starting</em><br>
        <strong>Step 1:</strong> Preheat stove to medium heat<br>
        <strong>Step 2:</strong> Place pan on stovetop<br>
        <strong>Step 3:</strong> butter all slices of bread on one side<br>
        <strong>Step 4:</strong> cook bacon in the pan on both sides to make sure it is not raw<br>
        <strong>Step 5:</strong> insert cheese, bacon, and meat between two slices of bread. <strong>BUTTERED SIDES FACING OUTWARDS</strong><br>
        <strong>Step 6:</strong> Place sandwiches on pan and flip when brownish colour. Repeat for other side<br>
        </p>
        <p><em>Source: <a href="https://www.delish.com/cooking/recipe-ideas/a19610233/how-to-make-best-grilled-cheese/">Other Grilled Cheese Recipe</a></em></p>
